        "subject": "LU-8964 llite: tunable ptasks number with optimized IO size",
        "message": "LU-8964 llite: tunable ptasks number with optimized IO size\n\nThe tunable llite.*.max_read_ptasks can be used to reduce the number\nof ptasks used in ll_readpages() used for async IO. Lower numbers than\nthe number of CPU cores are increasing performance with ZFS OSTs.\n\nThe number of pages handled by each ptask is now rounded to a multiple\nof 1MB, if possible, such that at most one of the async threads has\nan RPC which is not optimal. This increases chances for a nice stream\nof requests which are multiples of 1MB away from each other, thus\nhelping prefetch to see good patterns in sequential streams.\n\nChange-Id: Ie729a085b12e2c94bc542bdc846e7abeb4dbbfcb\nSigned-off-by: Erich Focht <efocht@hpce.nec.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
